modules.description: This module implements POSIX message queues for inter-process communication, supporting operations to open, send, receive, and manage message queues with priorities. It works with message queues identified by names like `/myqueue`, messages containing byte payloads and integer priorities, and queue attributes like maximum message count and size. Concrete use cases include coordinating tasks between processes, such as passing job data with varying priorities or synchronizing state changes across multiple processes.
